And at the end of days you will be asked a question:

"Which side were you on during the animal holocaust?"

For most of my life I had been on the side of the oppressors 

Yet now my eyes are wide open

@HollyFenwick No problem at all! Happy to answer any questions :) In fact you've inspired me to do something I've been meaning on doing for a looong time: to write up my long and winding journey to finally going vegan into an article. But here's the condensed version :)

@HollyFenwick I ate a lot of meat, dairy, and eggs growing up like any other kid. As an adult I was was an on again off again vegetarian/pescatarian for a long long time, same as quite a few of my friends...

@HollyFenwick It wasn't until I met Amy who had been vegan already for a few years that I started investigating and educating myself a bit more. It was a slow process of transition, watching documentaries and reading, but in the end it was clear in my mind that I had to give it a go.

@HollyFenwick We went along to a Brisbane Vegan Festival almost 3 years ago and watched a speech by James Aspey. After that I decided to try going 100% plant based as an experiment, to see how long I'd last... And so the experiment is still going strong.
@HollyFenwick Here is that exact speech from James Aspey anyway. It was filmed that afternoon in Brisbane. https://t.co/Sjjbyyr2tZ

@HollyFenwick It was a bit tough going in the beginning, but I was lucky to have Amy to help me out. In the end my only regret is not trying it sooner. Thanks for listening Holly anyway. I hope you have a wonderful night :)

@HollyFenwick You are already doing amazing good for the animals and the environment and for your health and wellbeing. Stay curious and open. It's a slow journey and yeah also not for everyone, at least not straight away. Enjoy James Aspey. There is a cut down version of it too :)
@HollyFenwick But the full speech is so amazing if you have the time ⏳
@lady_smock @HollyFenwick Even just cutting down gradually is good. We all do what we can. We are far from perfect too. And still learning. Onwards on the journey of life!
